attachments.title: Danwei Canting
attachments.text: Inspired by our lives in and travels to the Middle Kingdom, DĀNWÈI CĀNTĪNG (the Work Unit Restaurant) is a snapshot of the food and energy of Beijing. Our goal is to share Chinese home-style dishes (JIĀCHÁNG CÀI) with the people of Portland, using great technique and fresh local ingredients. Our name derives from the place where workers in China, up until the mid-1990’s would eat their meals. Since the members of the work unit came from all over China, the chef needed to be able to not only prepare local dishes but regional specialties as well. Our chef has created a menu which continues this tradition, bringing the best of China to the PDX Danwei.

text: I didn't like everything I tried there, but I did like the pork and green beans
As someone who is part Chinese I recommend the egg tarts.
they were out of the egg tarts when I went. love me some egg tarts.
I was pretty disappointed when I went (my bar for Chinese is pretty high), but I'll be happy to go back and try other dishes.
I had the crispy potatoes, cauliflower, lamb skewer, pork sando (no bread...) and the last time i went i had the fried chicken. i liked it all :grimacing:
